squiz/squizz
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:look, glance; esp. give (me, us) a squiz, a (quick) look, a peep
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1920 South Canterbury (G.L. Gabites) ca1935 Havelock schoolchildren e.g. G'is a squiz at your comic  ca1960 Wellington `still in use'
Citations
